  • Carrier/Reporter: Fedex Ground Package System, Inc.
  • Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Hazmat Injuries: 0
  • Non-Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Description: SequenceEvent: A package was discovered to be leaking at the loading area. Upon further inspection, it was determined that one out of four one-gallon bottles had a small crack/Puncture on its body resulting in the leakage. DescribePack: one out of four one-gallon bottles had a small crack/Puncture on its body at the bottom of the plastic bottle resulting in the leakage. DurationRel: 1 and MitigateEffect: upon the discovery of the package's leakage, it was promptly secured within a hazardous bag and subsequently transferred into a red tote to mitigate any potential for additional spillage.

  • Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Hazmat Injuries: 0

  • Description: SequenceEvent: PACKAGE FOUND LEAKING DURRING VAN LOAD. TOP OF BOX WAS WET FROM INNER LEAKAGE. THE OUTER PACKING WAS SIZED FOR 4 BOTTLES ONLY TWO WERE HOUSED WITHIN. CARDBOARD DIVIDERS WERE USED AS WELL AS PAPER PACKING TO TRY AND SUPPORT THE TWO BOTTLES. DescribePack: ONE OF THE BOTTLES WAS MISSING A CAP. CAP WAS FOUND IN THE ZIP LOCK BAG BOTTLE WAS SET IN. DurationRel: 2 and MitigateEffect: PACKAGE MOVED TO HAZMAT TOTE AND PLACED IN CAGE
